choice.default: High-quality standard checks with a low false positive rate.
choice.sensitive: Default checks + more comprehensive checks with a low false positive rate.
choice.security: Checkers that warn for potentially vulnerable code. Contains all SEI Cert C/C++ rules.
choice.portability: Checks that aim to detect code issues emerging from platform differences (eg. between 32-bit and 64-bit architectures).
choice.extreme: Sensitive checks + more comprehensive checks with a manageable false positive rate.

choice.STYLE: A true positive indicates that the source code is against a specific coding guideline or could improve readability.
choice.LOW: A true positive indicates that the source code is hard to read/understand or could be easily optimized.
choice.MEDIUM: A true positive indicates that the source code that may not cause a run-time error (yet), but against intuition and hence prone to error.
choice.HIGH: A true positive indicates that the source code will cause a run-time error.
choice.CRITICAL: Currently used for indicating compilation errors.
choice.UNSPECIFIED: Checker severity is not specified for a checker.
